Afterwards, the parameters were evaluated with respect to each scenario by assigning them a rank between one and ten (10 = best possible score). Those values were then multiplied by the respective weighting factor for the respective parameter established in the paired comparison and summed up as shown in Eq. 2, resulting in the final trade-off score (TOS). This score was then used during discussions with ESA representatives to put each scenario’s manufacturability into perspective and decide which three would be investigated further. All of the ten established scenarios are described in the Supplementary Material, where they are presented in descending order according to the analysis results:2TOS=T×wT+Tc×wTc+E×wE+Er×wEr+R×wR+Dp×wDp+A×wA+Bm×wBm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
